radiographic_examinations.findings: There are bibasilar atelectasis. The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated up to 13 mm with a hyperenhancing wall. Moderate periappendiceal fat stranding involving the mid appendix and appendiceal base at the origin from the cecum. Multiple bilateral simple renal cysts, the largest 4 x 3.5 cm at the left lower pole. Mild-to-moderate degenerative changes at L4/L5 and L5/S1.
